The paper deals with topological analysis and visualization of complex data sets, which is a common theme in computational geometry (cs.CG) and computer graphics (cs.GR). The use of mathematical structures such as Jacobi sets and Reeb spaces also suggests a connection to the subfield of computational topology (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the use of range and geometric measures for simplification, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and scientific visualization (cs.SI).
